By Cao Jin

Today is the 20th day of "Fengcheng" in Wuhan, the 12th order also refers to the early morning of February 11, the Wuhan new pneumonia epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters issued a circular No. 12 -- Foshan editor's note issued.

In these 20 days, I buy medicine to go out once, take express delivery to go out twice, buy mask, disinfectant, green vegetables to go out once. My family's food is getting less and less. I studied various online shopping apps, such as American cuisine, Meituan, Zhongbaidian, Youjia's store, eating and enjoying, Yangzi Yanxuan, etc. . Finally, I bought a box of eggs (360) and a box of mandarin oranges at Yangzi Yanxuan. Afternoon of the 9th. It could be here tomorrow. Took a lot of trouble, finally found the property group, see the group buy meat, each 5 Jin, there are 3 kinds, brisket, ribs, lean meat bought a, meat, eggs, fruit have landed.

I was urged to venture out by the community's announcement that one person per household could be sent out to buy food every three days. At 1:30 p.m. , with my hat, mask, and disposable gloves on, I stormed out of the store and bought salt, gravy, and steamed meat powder to prepare the meat I was about to receive, as well as four bags of paper towels and a box of milk. When the supermarket enters the door, must measure the body temperature, in the supermarket carries on the disinfection, the disinfection water's smell lets the human be at ease many. Want to buy flour, have not found, a ask only to know that flour is now particularly chic, 10:00 a. m. on a sell out, I catch in the supermarket before closing, do not think.

Since it's not easy to get out, let's go shopping. Rushing to the market, I am wearing a little less today, not wearing a sweater, but always feel cold back, sometimes a slight fever. The market is not a lot of people, I saw the opening of a fruit stall, I bought a bunch of bananas, 5 Jins of Sugar Tangerines, but also to the little guy at home to buy a dozen strawberries. Go to the food stall to buy food, potatoes, carrots, lettuce, scallions, vegetable moss, sweet potatoes, Bok Choy, mushrooms, winter melon, cucumber. Check out, my head is muddled, the boss said how much money is how much money, full of panic, feel their breath is fast. Vegetables and fruit are very heavy, I picked up very hard, in front of me about 10 meters there is an aunt, she said you find someone to help. I looked up, and there were just the two of us in the empty passageway, and I said I could do it. Take a few steps, stop for a change.

All the brain cells are trying to figure out what to do with the supplies to get them home. At last I filled the car to the brim. Calm down and ride home.

When approaching the gate of the residential area, the road was not smooth and the paper towel which was put in the back seat of the battery car fell down. I immediately stopped the car, turned around to see a just out of the community door of the mother-in-law picked up my drop that paper towel, turned around on a bicycle left. I didn't want to chase him either, because I didn't want to waste my breath, I didn't want to get in touch with anyone, and I didn't want to waste a minute outside. The thing is worthless, the key is rare to buy, out of a trip is not easy, need to muster up great courage, in case of infection.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When I got home, I changed my gloves and rearranged my supplies. Then go wash your hands, take a shower, and wash all your clothes with disinfectant.

I wiped my phone down with alcohol for five minutes and used up six alcohol swabs. I'd like to wash my cell phone with running water and hand sanitizer.

It's all set up. The little guy woke up from a nap. I feel a little tickle in my throat. I want to cough, but I can't. It shouldn't be a problem to play back all the details from today. But I'm a little worried.

Every time you want to cough, drink some water and take your temperature. Take the little guy's temperature every now and then. Worry! Come to think of it, the friend said she felt back pain, made a mental struggle to go to the hospital examination, the doctor said nothing. The next day she felt better, may be at home holding the baby back pain.

I want to get tested, to clear my head. Every morning when I wake up, I'm relieved to find that my family doesn't have any symptoms.

20 days after closing the city, I went out to buy some food. I was really scared. I wonder how long this life of fear will last, how I wish I could wake up one day and find that the epidemic is over, the quarantine is over, and we are free!
